1
00:01:36,888 --> 00:01:39,516
Yes, just like that.

2
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:41,109
You're doing well.

3
00:01:42,196 --> 00:01:44,373
Show the world now...

4
00:01:45,050 --> 00:01:46,694
the pianist...

5
00:01:46,694 --> 00:01:48,270
Seol Nae Il.

6
00:02:33,433 --> 00:02:37,487
She's following the score,
but adding her own feelings.

7
00:02:39,647 --> 00:02:41,110
Good.

8
00:02:41,110 --> 00:02:44,284
Just keep up what you are doing, Nae Il.

9
00:02:47,406 --> 00:02:51,193
She's the best so far.

10
00:02:51,193 --> 00:02:53,210
The sound is very colorful.

11
00:04:23,501 --> 00:04:26,387
Good job, Nae Il.

12
00:04:57,201 --> 00:04:58,711
Professor!

13
00:05:01,622 --> 00:05:07,026
I am the judge
for both the preliminary and final round.

14
00:05:07,026 --> 00:05:09,097
I'm only doing this because you asked.

15
00:05:09,996 --> 00:05:11,235
Thank you, Professor.

16
00:05:11,235 --> 00:05:13,776
Don't expect anything more.

17
00:05:13,776 --> 00:05:15,527
Nae Il is just a student

18
00:05:15,527 --> 00:05:19,318
who ran away
in the middle of my master class.

19
00:05:19,318 --> 00:05:21,786
I believe that changed as of today.

20
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:25,110
I was worried

21
00:05:25,110 --> 00:05:29,818
you wouldn't even listen to her performance
during the final round.

22
00:05:29,818 --> 00:05:33,965
Is there a reason you care so much for her?

23
00:05:36,741 --> 00:05:39,961
I want to see her grow as a pianist.

24
00:05:40,870 --> 00:05:42,652
That's why,

25
00:05:42,652 --> 00:05:46,175
I'm asking you to take a look at her
from a different perspective.

26
00:05:59,485 --> 00:06:02,246
When do the results come out?

27
00:06:02,841 --> 00:06:06,694
Professor, maybe I won't pass
the first round?

28
00:06:06,694 --> 00:06:08,652
I thought I did well today.

29
00:06:08,652 --> 00:06:10,901
What makes you feel so confident?

30
00:06:10,901 --> 00:06:12,610
Half of the contestants
don't pass the preliminary round.

31
00:06:12,610 --> 00:06:15,026
I have to win the competition!

32
00:06:15,026 --> 00:06:17,803
It can't be that tough
from the preliminary rounds.

33
00:06:25,735 --> 00:06:28,579
It's good to be confident,
but don't let your guard down.

34
00:06:30,295 --> 00:06:36,184
A performer's mind needs to be tight
like a fine-tuned piano.

35
00:06:36,884 --> 00:06:39,776
The moment
the performer gets arrogant and careless

36
00:06:39,776 --> 00:06:43,010
her performance becomes
loose and loses energy.

37
00:06:44,434 --> 00:06:46,444
My goodness.

38
00:06:47,562 --> 00:06:49,882
The list of people
who passed the preliminary round is out.

39
00:06:51,482 --> 00:06:53,200
Professor.

40
00:07:08,277 --> 00:07:12,694
Sunbae, I passed the preliminary round.

41
00:07:12,694 --> 00:07:14,125
Of course you did.

42
00:07:37,778 --> 00:07:39,901
Can you count this for me? For 15 people.

43
00:07:39,901 --> 00:07:41,277
Okay.

44
00:07:42,830 --> 00:07:44,423
What the...

45
00:07:53,544 --> 00:07:56,818
Su Min, something happened
between them, right?

46
00:07:56,818 --> 00:08:00,125
That's what I think, too.
It's right after they confessed their feelings.

47
00:08:03,054 --> 00:08:04,856
- Traitors.
- Traitors.

48
00:08:07,332 --> 00:08:09,543
Cha Yoo Jin is running late.

49
00:08:09,543 --> 00:08:11,386
I'll pass around the ballots first.

50
00:08:13,481 --> 00:08:14,440
Look at his mouth.

51
00:08:14,443 --> 00:08:16,422
- Oh my.
- Oh my.

52
00:08:18,135 --> 00:08:20,610
I'm sorry I'm late.

53
00:08:20,610 --> 00:08:24,318
Right, Nae Il had her preliminary round
performance today.

54
00:08:24,318 --> 00:08:27,318
I'm passing around the ballots now.
We'll begin right away.

55
00:08:27,318 --> 00:08:28,612
Okay.

56
00:09:07,952 --> 00:09:11,547
I'll announce the vote result.

57
00:09:14,694 --> 00:09:17,694
The one who received most votes
from A members.

58
00:09:17,694 --> 00:09:20,374
Yoo Il Lak,
who received a total of four votes.

59
00:09:23,735 --> 00:09:25,610
He will be the soloist
of the upcoming performance.

60
00:09:25,610 --> 00:09:27,706
Great!

61
00:09:29,245 --> 00:09:30,610
That's nonsense!

62
00:09:30,610 --> 00:09:34,402
Then the music will be
Tchaikovsky Violin Concerto in D major.

63
00:09:34,402 --> 00:09:35,402
We'll begin practicing tomorrow.

64
00:09:35,402 --> 00:09:37,565
Wait! Hey.

65
00:09:37,565 --> 00:09:39,360
How could I...

66
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,859
- Did something go wrong?
- Nothing went wrong.

67
00:09:41,859 --> 00:09:45,110
Everyone from S received one or two votes

68
00:09:45,110 --> 00:09:47,402
and A members also received one or two votes.

69
00:09:47,402 --> 00:09:50,621
Yoo Il Lak got four votes.
You have the most votes.

70
00:09:53,318 --> 00:09:58,110
I'll believe that everyone voted
for the sake of the orchestra.

71
00:09:58,110 --> 00:10:01,664
I believe there was no ulterior motive.

72
00:10:05,568 --> 00:10:07,402
Yes, I know I'm pretty good.

73
00:10:07,402 --> 00:10:10,110
You do have an eye for people.

74
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:15,002
But I really don't want to be a soloist.

75
00:10:18,752 --> 00:10:21,901
He says he doesn't want to,
so should we make him?

76
00:10:21,901 --> 00:10:24,235
Why don't we have Yoo Il Lak pick someone?

77
00:10:24,235 --> 00:10:26,447
Someone who suits the position.

78
00:10:26,447 --> 00:10:27,985
Right, yes yes.

79
00:10:27,985 --> 00:10:29,901
Shi Won is better than me.

80
00:10:29,901 --> 00:10:32,126
We all agreed.

81
00:10:32,820 --> 00:10:36,457
Whomever was voted would become the soloist.

82
00:10:50,973 --> 00:10:52,357
Cha Yoo Jin!

83
00:10:56,185 --> 00:10:58,821
Yoo Jin! Let's vote just one more time.

84
00:11:01,636 --> 00:11:05,565
You're the soloist.

85
00:11:07,322 --> 00:11:08,998
Are you upset?

86
00:11:09,997 --> 00:11:13,342
Are you upset because I became the soloist?

87
00:11:17,707 --> 00:11:19,383
Yes.

88
00:11:20,043 --> 00:11:21,761
Cha Yoo Jin.

89
00:11:23,402 --> 00:11:25,488
Those punks are looking down on you!

90
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:29,074
They did it knowing that you'd step down.

91
00:11:29,074 --> 00:11:31,752
They know you love the orchestra
more than anyone else.

92
00:11:32,811 --> 00:11:35,776
They knew that you'd be afraid
to mess up the concert

93
00:11:35,776 --> 00:11:37,365
and step down!

94
00:11:38,027 --> 00:11:40,402
That's why they voted for you.

95
00:11:40,402 --> 00:11:44,473
And you went along with them,
knowing what they did.

96
00:11:50,276 --> 00:11:55,156
Let's do a lesson for three hours each day
at your place.

97
00:11:55,156 --> 00:11:58,000
- What?
- You have to practice no matter what.

98
00:11:59,379 --> 00:12:01,765
So that they can't say anything.

99
00:12:08,758 --> 00:12:12,979
Hey, Yoo Jin,
do you like me a little too much?

100
00:12:13,971 --> 00:12:15,848
I am a little popular,

101
00:12:15,859 --> 00:12:18,578
but if you act this way,
it's too much for me!

102
00:12:27,235 --> 00:12:30,246
Thanks, Yoo Jin.

103
00:12:56,972 --> 00:12:59,267
Seol Nae Il, don't do anything stupid.

104
00:12:59,850 --> 00:13:02,193
That's disappointing.

105
00:13:02,193 --> 00:13:05,859
By the way, why didn't you reply to my text?

106
00:13:05,859 --> 00:13:08,318
I was waiting for you to congratulate me.

107
00:13:08,318 --> 00:13:10,776
It was just the preliminary round.

108
00:13:10,776 --> 00:13:13,318
Be happy that I went to see it.

109
00:13:13,318 --> 00:13:17,151
Still, tell me that I did well.

110
00:13:17,151 --> 00:13:18,848
You'll do better in the future.

111
00:13:31,132 --> 00:13:33,119
But they were too mean.

112
00:13:33,926 --> 00:13:36,266
He must've been a little disappointed.

113
00:13:37,095 --> 00:13:40,859
They didn't want a soloist
from the other team.

114
00:13:40,859 --> 00:13:42,610
It was also a surprise to me.

115
00:13:42,610 --> 00:13:46,542
Although they were fighting,
he cared for the orchestra.

116
00:13:47,857 --> 00:13:49,992
I didn't know they'd vote like that.

117
00:13:50,860 --> 00:13:53,652
Sunbae, are you really disappointed?

118
00:13:56,574 --> 00:13:58,751
Yes, a little.

119
00:14:03,455 --> 00:14:04,707
It's nice.

120
00:14:05,666 --> 00:14:08,800
You're telling me about your worries.

121
00:14:09,652 --> 00:14:12,401
I feel like we are a real couple.

122
00:14:14,582 --> 00:14:15,897
Do you have time for this?

123
00:14:15,897 --> 00:14:17,817
Aren't you going to prepare
for the second round?

124
00:14:21,349 --> 00:14:26,362
I hope the second round is also
with a composer I can become friends with.

125
00:14:39,534 --> 00:14:41,513
What about Schumann's Sonata?

126
00:14:42,402 --> 00:14:44,163
I don't know.

127
00:14:45,366 --> 00:14:47,542
You don't know Mussorgsky?

128
00:14:48,126 --> 00:14:51,527
You don't know Scriabin?
You don't know Prokofiev either?

129
00:14:51,527 --> 00:14:54,165
Proko... What?

130
00:14:56,117 --> 00:14:59,003
Just what kind of music
have you been practicing so far?

131
00:14:59,746 --> 00:15:02,235
The music that I liked.

132
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:07,665
"Dreams of Love" by Liszt,
"Moonlight Sonata" by Beethoven...

133
00:15:10,023 --> 00:15:12,492
That kind of music won't be included
in competitions.

134
00:15:13,610 --> 00:15:15,870
But they are good songs.

135
00:15:17,819 --> 00:15:18,838
Then...

136
00:15:19,610 --> 00:15:22,957
of course you wouldn't know
Chopin's Etude Op. 25.

137
00:15:24,329 --> 00:15:27,841
Chopin's Etude Op. 25?

138
00:15:31,923 --> 00:15:34,796
Why? Do you know it?

139
00:15:34,796 --> 00:15:37,471
It's No. 11 from Etude Op. 25.

140
00:15:37,985 --> 00:15:39,564
The highest difficulty.

141
00:15:41,471 --> 00:15:44,565
I played it before.

142
00:15:45,516 --> 00:15:48,777
My fingers probably remember it.

143
00:15:50,081 --> 00:15:53,259
Okay, play it then.

144
00:16:42,030 --> 00:16:45,443
Wow, look at Nae Il play the piano!
It's amazing!

145
00:16:45,443 --> 00:16:47,193
Teacher, come over here.

146
00:16:47,193 --> 00:16:49,333
Nae Il must be a genius.

147
00:17:01,838 --> 00:17:05,300
You already can play this?
You are truly amazing.

148
00:17:05,804 --> 00:17:09,110
Just do what I tell you to from now on.

149
00:17:09,110 --> 00:17:12,690
Then I will make you the best.

150
00:17:17,985 --> 00:17:20,568
She's not just good.

151
00:17:20,568 --> 00:17:23,151
She gives me chills.

152
00:17:23,151 --> 00:17:24,811
She's burning.

153
00:17:25,490 --> 00:17:28,411
A pianist that moves people's heart.

154
00:17:52,018 --> 00:17:54,237
Is this the music for the second round?

155
00:17:55,647 --> 00:17:57,782
She's really good.

156
00:17:58,650 --> 00:18:00,283
Nae Il's piano...

157
00:18:01,151 --> 00:18:03,830
Why did it take so long
to be out in the world?

158
00:18:06,324 --> 00:18:13,214
She's like a treasure
I want to show everyone...

159
00:18:14,123 --> 00:18:16,634
but I want to keep her hidden, too.

160
00:18:17,961 --> 00:18:19,762
I'm nervous.

161
00:18:22,340 --> 00:18:24,517
You feel the same way, right?

162
00:18:25,610 --> 00:18:28,488
I don't know what you're talking about.

163
00:18:28,488 --> 00:18:30,915
What? "My treasure"?

164
00:18:32,432 --> 00:18:36,521
Keeping her hidden
or bragging about her to the world,

165
00:18:37,312 --> 00:18:39,476
it's for her to decide.

166
00:18:40,358 --> 00:18:42,451
She isn't some object.

167
00:18:45,321 --> 00:18:47,957
I'm transferring
to the conducting major in Han Eum.

168
00:18:49,926 --> 00:18:52,859
I thought I wouldn't be able
to give up cello,

169
00:18:52,859 --> 00:18:56,733
but now I want to try conducting.

170
00:19:11,318 --> 00:19:14,943
Yoon Hoo is transferring
to the conducting major?

171
00:19:14,943 --> 00:19:18,242
I heard you recommended him.
Why didn't you tell me?

172
00:19:18,242 --> 00:19:20,711
Is it a big deal?

173
00:19:24,921 --> 00:19:27,529
It's not a big deal.

174
00:19:27,529 --> 00:19:29,205
Why did you call me here?

175
00:19:31,242 --> 00:19:35,587
Should the teacher and his pupil go
on a trip to Europe?

176
00:19:37,151 --> 00:19:38,344
Europe?

177
00:19:39,110 --> 00:19:40,402
Are you running away again...

178
00:19:40,402 --> 00:19:42,532
I'm not running away.

179
00:19:42,532 --> 00:19:45,985
I'll be absent just for a while
to take you with me.

180
00:19:45,985 --> 00:19:48,546
I received Mi Na's permission.

181
00:19:49,778 --> 00:19:52,318
If you need a busboy again...

182
00:19:52,318 --> 00:19:54,719
Aren't you going to go study abroad?

183
00:19:55,849 --> 00:19:59,854
It's the national music academy
that everyone wants to go.

184
00:19:59,859 --> 00:20:03,250
After you graduate,
will you conduct Rising Star?

185
00:20:07,235 --> 00:20:10,943
Is it because of Baby?

186
00:20:10,943 --> 00:20:16,179
Didn't you make Baby enter the competition
to go study abroad?

187
00:20:18,393 --> 00:20:20,360
If Baby wins the competition,

188
00:20:20,360 --> 00:20:22,989
she will get a chance to study in Europe.

189
00:20:24,434 --> 00:20:26,694
Aren't you going with her?

190
00:20:36,014 --> 00:20:38,059
Those punks are looking down on you!

191
00:20:38,068 --> 00:20:40,818
They did it knowing that you'd step down.

192
00:20:40,818 --> 00:20:43,164
They know you love the orchestra
more than anyone else.

193
00:20:51,365 --> 00:20:53,318
Are you feeling down?

194
00:20:53,318 --> 00:20:54,861
You have no appetite?

195
00:20:55,644 --> 00:20:57,238
Try this.

196
00:20:57,238 --> 00:21:00,708
Your appetite that ran away
will come back like Usain Bolt.

197
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:07,874
My son is a soloist,
you really must not get sick.

198
00:21:07,874 --> 00:21:11,424
Right? I'm a soloist now.

199
00:21:11,424 --> 00:21:13,221
I shouldn't get sick.

200
00:21:25,231 --> 00:21:27,575
Yoo Il Lak, the soloist of Rising Star!

201
00:21:28,228 --> 00:21:30,318
Don't do that. You're embarrassing me.

202
00:21:30,318 --> 00:21:31,776
What's to be embarrassed about?

203
00:21:31,776 --> 00:21:35,068
It wouldn't be enough
if you walked around with a post on your back.

204
00:21:35,068 --> 00:21:37,485
I'm sorry that I'm really popular.

205
00:21:37,485 --> 00:21:39,612
You'd have been picked if it wasn't for me.

206
00:21:39,612 --> 00:21:42,859
Why are you sorry? I voted for you, too.

207
00:21:42,859 --> 00:21:47,318
I can't help that Il Lak is attractive
as a human being and as a violinist.

208
00:21:47,318 --> 00:21:49,443
You're more than qualified.

209
00:21:49,443 --> 00:21:51,715
Really? You think that way?

210
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:54,718
So you really fell deep into my soul.

211
00:21:55,677 --> 00:21:59,776
I guess my performance lacks soul.
I didn't get many votes.

212
00:21:59,776 --> 00:22:01,568
Not at all!

213
00:22:01,568 --> 00:22:04,985
I'm a live witness who fell into your soul!

214
00:22:04,985 --> 00:22:07,815
I wrote down your name, too.
So don't say that.

215
00:22:08,732 --> 00:22:11,943
It's true that I was disappointed at first
because it wasn't me.

216
00:22:11,943 --> 00:22:14,029
But you're qualified.

217
00:22:14,029 --> 00:22:16,859
So don't be sorry and do well!

218
00:22:16,859 --> 00:22:17,997
Yeah.

219
00:22:18,743 --> 00:22:21,507
I'll make sure
that those punks keep quiet.

220
00:23:25,110 --> 00:23:28,527
Do we have to accompany that solo?

221
00:23:28,527 --> 00:23:29,692
Right?

222
00:23:30,438 --> 00:23:32,900
My oboe is wasted on him.

223
00:23:46,381 --> 00:23:51,026
I think it'll be better
to speed up for the solo part.

224
00:23:51,026 --> 00:23:53,021
Okay, got it.

225
00:23:54,473 --> 00:23:56,441
Let's take a 10 minute break.

226
00:24:12,565 --> 00:24:14,962
Sunbae, are you sick?

227
00:24:15,901 --> 00:24:17,735
No, not at all.

228
00:24:17,735 --> 00:24:19,798
Then what's with your performance?

229
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:24,085
It's the first time
he's playing with the orchestra.

230
00:24:24,797 --> 00:24:28,485
First time, my butt. Isn't he embarrassed?

231
00:24:28,485 --> 00:24:30,850
He has to rehearse with the orchestra to know.

232
00:24:32,677 --> 00:24:34,527
It would've been the same for you all.

233
00:24:34,527 --> 00:24:36,940
- Me?
- No way.

234
00:25:06,868 --> 00:25:08,901
Seol Nae Il.

235
00:25:08,901 --> 00:25:10,735
You make a lot of mistakes on the octaves.

236
00:25:10,735 --> 00:25:12,026
Didn't you practice?

237
00:25:12,026 --> 00:25:14,318
Do you want to stay up all night?

238
00:25:14,318 --> 00:25:15,985
Back to the beginning.

239
00:25:15,985 --> 00:25:18,110
Practice 100 times.

240
00:25:18,110 --> 00:25:20,694
If you make more mistakes,
you have to practice 1000 times.

241
00:25:20,694 --> 00:25:22,652
Focus!

242
00:25:24,263 --> 00:25:28,483
No, don't think about anything else.

243
00:25:28,483 --> 00:25:32,579
Just think about winning the competition
and going to Europe with Yoo Jin.

244
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,735
Milch.

245
00:26:44,735 --> 00:26:48,947
I heard about your results
and came here to congratulate you.

246
00:26:51,305 --> 00:26:54,816
But what's with your face, Baby?

247
00:26:56,825 --> 00:27:02,171
Do you have a bad memory
concerning this music?

248
00:27:03,495 --> 00:27:06,373
Can you see that?

249
00:27:06,373 --> 00:27:12,387
A performer's mind shows in her performance.

250
00:27:13,068 --> 00:27:16,697
With this Chopin's Etude,

251
00:27:16,697 --> 00:27:20,068
fast development of arpeggio
by the right hand

252
00:27:20,068 --> 00:27:24,735
reminds people of a harsh winter wind,

253
00:27:24,735 --> 00:27:27,527
so it's called 'Winter Wind.'

254
00:27:27,527 --> 00:27:35,527
But there is a harsher wind on your face
than the arpeggio.

255
00:27:40,688 --> 00:27:43,818
I'm sorry.
I keep thinking about something else.

256
00:27:43,818 --> 00:27:46,227
Don't be.

257
00:27:46,227 --> 00:27:51,490
Use your feelings and let them all out!

258
00:27:53,526 --> 00:28:01,276
Pour your anger and emotional garbage
into your performance.

259
00:28:01,276 --> 00:28:05,694
That will help create your own performance.

260
00:28:05,694 --> 00:28:09,424
Throw everything in the performance.

261
00:28:10,584 --> 00:28:12,386
After that...

262
00:28:14,847 --> 00:28:19,017
you can go back to your happy self as usual.

263
00:28:20,003 --> 00:28:20,818
Milch.

264
00:28:20,818 --> 00:28:25,983
You have nothing to be afraid of
in front of the piano, Baby!

265
00:28:27,610 --> 00:28:30,235
I'll do what you told me to do.

266
00:28:30,235 --> 00:28:32,656
I won't avoid it.

267
00:28:47,385 --> 00:28:50,670
Il Lak, did your fingers get stiff already?

268
00:28:51,217 --> 00:28:54,387
Why did you stop your vibrato?
You did well before.

269
00:28:54,387 --> 00:28:57,776
I thought you'd say
I'm only following my feeling.

270
00:28:57,776 --> 00:29:00,110
It's okay to follow your feeling.

271
00:29:00,110 --> 00:29:03,818
You are a bit overconfident,

272
00:29:03,818 --> 00:29:05,360
but don't abandon it.

273
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:07,659
A performer needs his pride.

274
00:29:08,218 --> 00:29:12,193
People who listen to this concerto...
How should I say this?

275
00:29:12,193 --> 00:29:14,776
They will be listening to your soul.

276
00:29:14,776 --> 00:29:16,901
Really?

277
00:29:16,901 --> 00:29:18,735
So I can spread my soul all I want?

278
00:29:18,735 --> 00:29:20,443
But don't go too far.

279
00:29:20,443 --> 00:29:23,235
Only as far as not ruining the music.

280
00:29:23,235 --> 00:29:28,882
Of course.
I'm really not the Yoo Il Lak I used to be.

281
00:29:55,074 --> 00:29:57,334
Il Lak, all the best!

282
00:30:12,550 --> 00:30:14,477
Sunbae!

283
00:30:31,527 --> 00:30:34,485
You make it so obvious
that you're disappointed.

284
00:30:34,485 --> 00:30:35,818
Were you waiting for Yoo Jin?

285
00:30:35,818 --> 00:30:37,833
I'm not.

286
00:30:39,485 --> 00:30:43,996
By the way, Yoon Hoo,
do you go somewhere these days?

287
00:30:43,996 --> 00:30:46,276
I see you often in school,

288
00:30:46,276 --> 00:30:48,776
but I heard
you don't come to the practice room.

289
00:30:48,776 --> 00:30:51,652
Lak is really disappointed.

290
00:30:51,652 --> 00:30:54,083
Maybe because A members are there too.

291
00:30:54,083 --> 00:30:57,427
I still feel a bit unfamiliar
with Rising Star.

292
00:30:58,352 --> 00:31:02,405
To be honest,
Rising Star is a bit difficult for me, too.

293
00:31:03,144 --> 00:31:05,485
You should wait inside.

294
00:31:05,485 --> 00:31:07,646
My Nae Il's nose is red.

295
00:31:17,485 --> 00:31:20,985
I'm not your Nae Il, Yoon Hoo.

296
00:31:20,985 --> 00:31:26,335
If you keep making fun of me like this,
it'll look like you like me.

297
00:31:27,537 --> 00:31:31,007
What if I like you? Can't I?

298
00:31:33,485 --> 00:31:35,140
No, you can't.

299
00:31:36,134 --> 00:31:38,728
I'm going inside.

300
00:31:48,646 --> 00:31:51,157
I shouldn't have rushed.

301
00:32:11,794 --> 00:32:13,976
I got rejected by Nae Il.

302
00:32:17,115 --> 00:32:18,917
Of course.

303
00:32:22,370 --> 00:32:23,776
Why are you telling me this?

304
00:32:23,776 --> 00:32:26,110
I have no one to talk to.

305
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:27,360
Go to your best friends.

306
00:32:27,360 --> 00:32:29,360
They don't know what to do.

307
00:32:29,360 --> 00:32:31,387
It'll be hard for them to take sides.

308
00:32:34,859 --> 00:32:36,494
You haven't had many friends, have you?

309
00:32:37,427 --> 00:32:39,943
You only want to show them your good side

310
00:32:39,943 --> 00:32:42,315
and you carry everything by yourself.

311
00:32:43,014 --> 00:32:45,274
I can see that you're not used to it.

312
00:32:48,623 --> 00:32:50,842
That's from your own experience, right?

313
00:32:54,775 --> 00:32:56,785
Hang out with yourself.

314
00:32:58,174 --> 00:33:01,643
We're on a ceasefire
until Nae Il wins the competition.

315
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:05,339
I've never fought with you.

316
00:33:07,056 --> 00:33:09,443
You're disappointing me. Don't do that.

317
00:33:09,443 --> 00:33:11,859
I plan to follow Nae Il to her study abroad

318
00:33:11,859 --> 00:33:15,014
then we might see each other for a long time.

319
00:33:19,678 --> 00:33:22,730
Aren't you going?

320
00:33:26,744 --> 00:33:29,004
Yoo Jin! Yoo Jin!

321
00:33:34,442 --> 00:33:35,943
College orchestra festival?

322
00:33:35,943 --> 00:33:40,031
We'll enter it with the concerto music
with Il Lak as the soloist?

323
00:33:40,031 --> 00:33:43,585
And record for a TV program at the same time?

324
00:33:45,193 --> 00:33:47,318
We still have a lot of time,
so what's to worry?

325
00:33:47,318 --> 00:33:49,943
Besides, Il Lak is getting better.

326
00:33:49,943 --> 00:33:52,026
- Isn't that right?
- Yes, yes.

327
00:33:52,026 --> 00:33:54,794
Il Lak got much better all of a sudden.

328
00:33:57,565 --> 00:34:00,276
Mini Min Hee, don't fall for me though.

329
00:34:00,276 --> 00:34:03,276
- How annoying.
- Seriously, How annoying.

330
00:34:03,276 --> 00:34:05,735
We're against Sae Hyun on the last day?

331
00:34:05,735 --> 00:34:07,257
We should really practice.

332
00:34:07,257 --> 00:34:11,352
I think
Sae Yeon's conductor studied in Germany.

333
00:34:12,387 --> 00:34:14,981
The rumor has it that he's really good.

334
00:34:46,783 --> 00:34:48,585
Yeah?

335
00:34:52,193 --> 00:34:56,030
Yoo Jin, the music for the second round
is by a composer I'm familiar with.

336
00:34:56,030 --> 00:35:00,026
I'm not friends with him,
but I'll do my best with my performance

337
00:35:00,026 --> 00:35:01,943
so you have to come.

338
00:35:01,943 --> 00:35:04,881
I'll only pass if you come.

339
00:35:31,828 --> 00:35:33,527
Kim Ga Ram.

340
00:35:33,527 --> 00:35:37,550
I heard she's a contender,
and she's really good.

341
00:35:58,062 --> 00:36:00,489
Number 40, on stand-by please.

342
00:36:12,916 --> 00:36:15,335
Sir, I'll get out here.

343
00:36:16,068 --> 00:36:17,798
Thank you.

344
00:36:26,068 --> 00:36:27,745
Seol Nae Il?

345
00:36:28,549 --> 00:36:31,318
She played Haydn beautifully last time.

346
00:36:31,318 --> 00:36:34,418
It's easy to remember her
because she has a unique name.

347
00:36:45,235 --> 00:36:46,672
You came, Professor.

348
00:36:46,672 --> 00:36:48,859
You asked me to come for the first round,

349
00:36:48,859 --> 00:36:51,443
so why didn't you ask me
to come to the second?

350
00:36:51,443 --> 00:36:53,812
Because I knew you'd come.

351
00:37:17,328 --> 00:37:18,694
Look at that.

352
00:37:18,694 --> 00:37:21,123
What's with her face
when she wants to win the competition?

353
00:37:21,123 --> 00:37:24,543
What's with her face, by the way?

354
00:37:24,543 --> 00:37:27,610
She looks like she doesn't want to be here.

355
00:37:27,610 --> 00:37:29,681
I'm not sure.

356
00:38:32,985 --> 00:38:35,943
She just poured too much in.

357
00:38:35,943 --> 00:38:38,498
My goodness, it's too fast.

358
00:39:30,356 --> 00:39:35,029
It wasn't enough to burn, it became ashes.

359
00:39:36,114 --> 00:39:38,166
It's over.

360
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:54,801
I messed it up.

361
00:39:55,818 --> 00:39:58,411
What do I do, Sunbae?

362
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:02,610
Did we select all the finalists?

363
00:40:02,610 --> 00:40:06,701
No, the last student is a problem.

364
00:40:06,701 --> 00:40:08,568
Oh, Seol Nae Il?

365
00:40:08,568 --> 00:40:11,694
Didn't she go beyond unique
and go messy with her own style?

366
00:40:11,694 --> 00:40:13,443
But wasn't it really attractive?

367
00:40:13,443 --> 00:40:17,859
But the competition is
about being precise by the rules.

368
00:40:17,859 --> 00:40:20,318
- That shouldn't be ignored.
- You're right.

369
00:40:20,318 --> 00:40:24,676
Once the rule is broken, chaos is created
and it's hard to keep score.

370
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:34,276
Seol Nae Il, this kid.

371
00:40:34,276 --> 00:40:36,906
I begged her to strictly follow the score.

372
00:40:36,906 --> 00:40:37,901
What about Seol Nae Il?

373
00:40:37,901 --> 00:40:40,293
She's hiding in the bathroom.

374
00:40:41,135 --> 00:40:44,443
She really messed up,
I'm sure she can't face reality.

375
00:40:44,443 --> 00:40:46,466
It was a good performance.

376
00:40:48,419 --> 00:40:50,804
It just didn't suit the competition.

377
00:40:51,562 --> 00:40:54,317
Do you think that makes sense?

378
00:40:54,318 --> 00:40:58,193
If she decided to join the competition,
she should follow the rules!

379
00:40:58,193 --> 00:41:00,480
She made an effort in her own way.

380
00:41:01,301 --> 00:41:03,562
Don't be too harsh on her.

381
00:41:04,465 --> 00:41:06,485
- The result is out.
- Really?

382
00:41:06,485 --> 00:41:08,041
- Let's see.
- Where is it?

383
00:41:12,720 --> 00:41:15,694
She wouldn't make it anyway.

384
00:41:15,694 --> 00:41:17,246
Why should I bother to look?

385
00:41:32,276 --> 00:41:33,318
There.

386
00:41:33,318 --> 00:41:34,751
[Seol Nae Il]

387
00:41:35,245 --> 00:41:37,625
There she is, Seol Nae Il.

388
00:41:42,070 --> 00:41:42,859
Excuse me.

389
00:41:42,859 --> 00:41:44,568
Excuse me, excuse me.

390
00:41:44,568 --> 00:41:46,150
Excuse me.

391
00:41:48,978 --> 00:41:50,694
It's true.

392
00:41:50,694 --> 00:41:54,026
Competitions have changed.

393
00:41:54,026 --> 00:41:55,826
They have evolved!

394
00:42:07,901 --> 00:42:13,818
It's too bad,
but let's drop Seol Nae Il then.

395
00:42:13,818 --> 00:42:18,110
I'd like to hear more of her performance.

396
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:21,125
Her performance is full of her emotions.

397
00:42:22,402 --> 00:42:26,151
It's different from a mechanical performance
that follows a metronome.

398
00:42:26,151 --> 00:42:28,583
I really like
that it feels like a human being.

399
00:42:30,026 --> 00:42:33,985
Don't you wonder
about how she will perform next time?

400
00:42:33,985 --> 00:42:39,485
Right, Professor?
I agree 100 percent with you.

401
00:42:39,485 --> 00:42:42,377
To be honest, I do want to hear
a little more of her performances.

402
00:42:57,366 --> 00:42:59,209
Please answer your phone.

403
00:42:59,209 --> 00:43:01,568
[Cha Yoo Jin]

404
00:43:05,375 --> 00:43:07,844
I'm sorry, Yoo Jin.

405
00:43:08,751 --> 00:43:12,638
I'm so embarrassed right now,
I can't answer your call.

406
00:43:28,938 --> 00:43:30,993
You passed the second round.

407
00:43:30,993 --> 00:43:34,451
So just come out now, idiot.

408
00:43:44,287 --> 00:43:46,047
Sunbae!

409
00:43:48,234 --> 00:43:51,118
Sunbae, you came!

410
00:43:51,118 --> 00:43:53,868
I think I passed thanks to you!

411
00:43:53,868 --> 00:43:54,909
Get away from me!

412
00:43:54,909 --> 00:43:56,650
- I'm so happy.
- Oh, my goodness.

413
00:43:57,631 --> 00:43:59,826
Now, it's the final round.

414
00:43:59,826 --> 00:44:02,582
You have no time to play. Let's go.

415
00:44:03,512 --> 00:44:05,600
Sunbae!

416
00:44:14,231 --> 00:44:16,319
You don't even need to check.

417
00:44:16,326 --> 00:44:19,461
I'm sure my Ga Ram passed the second round
with the highest score.

418
00:44:25,995 --> 00:44:27,588
Seol Nae Il?

419
00:44:28,915 --> 00:44:30,909
She entered the competition?

420
00:44:30,909 --> 00:44:32,844
Do you know her?

421
00:44:33,583 --> 00:44:36,702
There can't be two people with that name.

422
00:44:36,702 --> 00:44:39,035
It's probably her.

423
00:44:39,035 --> 00:44:40,951
Is she good?

424
00:44:40,951 --> 00:44:43,577
She's born with her talent.

425
00:44:43,577 --> 00:44:46,368
But you don't need to worry.

426
00:44:46,368 --> 00:44:49,332
I'm not sure how she passed the second round,

427
00:44:49,332 --> 00:44:52,635
but she's not the kind
who is able to get through a competition.

428
00:44:53,564 --> 00:44:56,826
Competition is not
as big a deal as I thought.

429
00:45:06,452 --> 00:45:08,371
You're full of yourself again?

430
00:45:08,371 --> 00:45:09,826
What did I tell you?

431
00:45:09,826 --> 00:45:11,841
I told you not to lose your focus.

432
00:45:12,895 --> 00:45:14,993
Do you know any of the music here?

433
00:45:14,993 --> 00:45:16,720
Let me see.

434
00:45:23,511 --> 00:45:25,271
No.

435
00:45:25,843 --> 00:45:27,909
I knew it.

436
00:45:27,909 --> 00:45:29,817
Which one will be good?

437
00:45:32,542 --> 00:45:35,459
[La Campanella]

438
00:45:37,016 --> 00:45:39,209
Yes, Liszt.

439
00:45:39,209 --> 00:45:42,243
Let's go with La Campanella by Liszt.

440
00:45:42,243 --> 00:45:44,201
La Campanella?

441
00:45:44,201 --> 00:45:45,493
Yes.

442
00:45:45,493 --> 00:45:47,535
He admired Paganini.

443
00:45:47,535 --> 00:45:50,035
Liszt who wanted
to become the Paganini of pianists

444
00:45:50,035 --> 00:45:51,577
made this daring move.

445
00:45:51,577 --> 00:45:54,227
Technique like no other!

446
00:45:56,199 --> 00:45:58,376
This music is perfect for you.

447
00:45:59,270 --> 00:46:01,572
Yes, I'll do my best!

448
00:46:09,535 --> 00:46:10,703
Congratulations.

449
00:46:10,703 --> 00:46:13,923
There must've been a lot of competitors,
but you were lucky.

450
00:46:16,436 --> 00:46:20,493
I guess so.
I didn't know this would happen so fast.

451
00:46:20,493 --> 00:46:22,744
It must be nice.

452
00:46:22,744 --> 00:46:25,535
Kaiduhoon.

453
00:46:25,535 --> 00:46:29,751
To get lessons
from the leader of the Berlin string quartet.

454
00:46:29,751 --> 00:46:30,459
Yes.

455
00:46:30,459 --> 00:46:33,459
You're going to be very busy now.

456
00:46:33,459 --> 00:46:36,688
- You may leave.
- Yes. Thank you.

457
00:47:55,667 --> 00:47:59,680
Practice more on your own
so that you don't interrupt the soloist.

458
00:48:01,230 --> 00:48:03,699
You know who you are.

459
00:48:12,392 --> 00:48:15,528
That's it for today. Good job.

460
00:48:44,792 --> 00:48:48,262
What now?
You can practice on your own now.

461
00:48:48,626 --> 00:48:50,417
It's not that.

462
00:48:50,417 --> 00:48:51,709
What I'm trying to say is...

463
00:48:51,709 --> 00:48:54,012
Just tell me what's on your mind.

464
00:48:54,685 --> 00:48:56,069
It's...

465
00:48:58,397 --> 00:49:00,616
Will I make a mistake on stage?

466
00:49:01,626 --> 00:49:02,876
What?

467
00:49:02,876 --> 00:49:05,888
If you have time to worry about that,
go practice.

468
00:49:06,626 --> 00:49:07,695
Why?

469
00:49:07,695 --> 00:49:10,088
I heard we'll be on stage with Sae-Yeon.

470
00:49:10,088 --> 00:49:11,918
I have no idea

471
00:49:11,918 --> 00:49:15,518
how the pressure from that stage
will change me.

472
00:49:16,945 --> 00:49:18,417
What do you want to say?

473
00:49:18,417 --> 00:49:20,940
So, I mean...

474
00:49:24,626 --> 00:49:28,375
Can we change the soloist to Shi Won?

475
00:49:28,375 --> 00:49:31,007
Leave. Stop saying nonsense.

476
00:49:31,007 --> 00:49:33,167
It's not nonsense.

477
00:49:33,167 --> 00:49:37,459
It's such an important performance,
Shi Won is much better than I am.

478
00:49:37,459 --> 00:49:39,375
I will never change it.

479
00:49:39,375 --> 00:49:40,600
Where did your spirit and passion go

480
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:42,568
when you said
you wanted make it a great performance?

481
00:49:43,528 --> 00:49:45,667
You're talking like a weakling.

482
00:49:45,667 --> 00:49:49,667
If you keep practicing like now,
it'll be a great performance.

483
00:49:49,667 --> 00:49:51,369
So practice.

484
00:49:54,036 --> 00:49:56,088
Hey.

485
00:50:13,931 --> 00:50:16,567
I missed on the fourth finger and the pinky.

486
00:50:18,834 --> 00:50:21,858
No, no, the rhythm is wrong.

487
00:50:23,187 --> 00:50:26,292
This is the sound of a bell. Sound of a bell.

488
00:50:26,292 --> 00:50:28,447
More delicately.

489
00:50:49,591 --> 00:50:51,115
It's complete.

490
00:50:51,844 --> 00:50:53,899
She's playing it the way she should.

491
00:50:54,549 --> 00:50:57,510
I didn't teach her this.

492
00:50:57,510 --> 00:51:02,565
How can such a human being exist?

493
00:51:52,398 --> 00:51:55,868
Cha Yoo Jin, I need your help.

494
00:52:26,542 --> 00:52:28,584
She's reckless.

495
00:52:45,999 --> 00:52:50,261
Sunbae, let's go to Europe together.

496
00:52:51,584 --> 00:52:53,837
It would be nice if we could.

497
00:52:53,837 --> 00:52:57,681
I'll make sure to send you to Europe.

498
00:53:00,125 --> 00:53:02,167
Thanks for saying that.

499
00:53:02,167 --> 00:53:06,256
I should do my best
not to fall behind Seol Nae Il.

500
00:53:06,256 --> 00:53:09,416
I won't fall behind you either.

501
00:53:10,107 --> 00:53:14,703
I will do my best
so that I don't embarrass you.

502
00:53:17,584 --> 00:53:19,670
You don't need to win the competition.

503
00:53:20,656 --> 00:53:22,709
You were right.

504
00:53:22,709 --> 00:53:25,809
Freely, happily...

505
00:53:27,291 --> 00:53:29,718
play it the way you want.

506
00:53:30,454 --> 00:53:33,042
You have to be happy when you play,

507
00:53:33,042 --> 00:53:35,610
for the people listening to your music
to be happy.

508
00:53:37,342 --> 00:53:39,978
You've changed a lot.

509
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:45,053
Still, I'm definitely going
to win the competition.

510
00:53:47,019 --> 00:53:49,655
Do whatever you want.

511
00:54:08,918 --> 00:54:11,000
Mini Min Hee, what are you making?

512
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:12,596
Boss.

513
00:54:13,462 --> 00:54:14,605
What's this?

514
00:54:15,375 --> 00:54:17,918
Seol Nae Il, fighting. Seol Nae Il...

515
00:54:17,918 --> 00:54:19,167
Did Nae Il enter some competition?

516
00:54:19,167 --> 00:54:21,252
Yes, she made it
to the final round of a competition.

517
00:54:21,252 --> 00:54:22,918
So I'm going to go cheer her on.

518
00:54:22,918 --> 00:54:25,042
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

519
00:54:25,042 --> 00:54:26,932
I should go cheer for her too.

520
00:54:28,515 --> 00:54:31,209
Mini Min Hee, be my sidekick.

521
00:54:31,209 --> 00:54:32,605
What?

522
00:54:40,822 --> 00:54:42,441
We have to do well.

523
00:54:43,601 --> 00:54:45,569
